<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.280080>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Map of the type locality of Paranaichthys longianalis gen. et sp. nov. (Brazilian states: RS, Rio Grande do Sul; SC, Santa Catarina; PR, Paraná, SP, São Paulo; MG, Minas Gerais; MS, Mato Grosso do Sul; MT, Mato Grosso; GO, Goiás; DF, Distrito Federal; RJ, Rio de Janeiro; ES, Espírito Santo; BA, Bahia)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/280080/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.280082>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Photograph of the holotype (MCP – 3371 – PV) of Paranaichthys longianalis gen. et sp. nov.; Scale bar = cm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/280082/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.280083>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Camera lucida drawing of specimen MCP – 3371 – PV of Paranaichthys longianalis gen. et sp. nov." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/280083/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.280085>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Proposed reconstruction of Paranaichthys longianalis gen. et sp. nov. Illustration by Eduardo Kickhöfel." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/280085/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.280084>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Detail of the skull of Paranaichthys longianalis gen. et sp. nov. (MCP – 3371 – PV); question marks indicate unidentified or dubious bone fragments. Abbreviations: cd, crushing dentition; cl, cleithrum; d, dentary; dh, dermohyal; dpt, dermopterotic; dsph, dermosphenotic; ex, extrascapula; f, frontal; mx, maxilla; nr, nostril; od, odontodes; op, operculum; pa, parietal; pop?, preoperculum?; pr, postrostral; psph, parasphenoid; pt, post-temporal; r-pmx, rostro-premaxilla; scl, supracleithrum; sop, suboperculum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/280084/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.280086>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Skull bones tentatively identified and positioned in the reconstruction of Paranaichthys longianalis gen. et sp. nov. Abbreviations: cd, crushing dentition; cl, cleithrum; d, dentary; dh, dermohyal; dpt, dermopterotic; dsph, dermosphenotic; ex, extrascapula; f, frontal; mx, maxilla; nr, nostril; od, odontodes; op, operculum; pa, parietal; pop?, preoperculum?; pr, postrostral; psph, parasphenoid; pt, post-temporal; r-pmx, rostro-premaxilla; scl, supracleithrum; sop, suboperculum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/280086/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.280087>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. A, Photograph of the crushing dentition of Paranaichthys longianalis in the parasphenoid. B, Tooth cross-section. C, Interpretative drawing of the tooth. D, Detail of verruciform acrodin. Abbreviations: cd, crushing dentition; de, dentine; dt, dentine tubules; e, enamel; pc, pulp cavity; psph, parasphenoid; vacr, verruciform acrodin." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/280087/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.280088>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. A, Photograph of the cross-section of a skull dermal bone (maxilla) under light microscopy. B, Interpretative illustration of the cross-section. Odontodes on transverse section on the right, with evidence of superpositional growth and a more longitudinal section on the left side. Abbreviations: de, dentine; dt, dentine tubules; g, ganoine; is, isopedine; od, odontodes; os, osteocite lacune; pc, pulp cavity; vc, vascular canal." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/280088/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.280081>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Measurements taken on the reconstruction of Paranaichthys longianalis gen. et sp. nov. a, total length; b, standard length; c, body length; d, trunk length; e, head length; f, caudal peduncle length; g, caudal fin length; h, total length of the caudal region; i, caudal fin height; j, caudal peduncle height; k, estimated body height; l, head height; m, posterior anal fin length; n, anterior anal fin length; o, anal fin base length; p, pelvic fin height; q, pelvic fin base length; r, pectoral fin width; s, pectoral fin length; t, frontal bone length." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/280081/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.280089>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. A, Stereomicroscopic photograph of trunk scales coated with ammonium chloride. B – C, Scanning Electron microscopic images of a fulcral scale of the caudal peduncle. Abbreviations: fw, furrows on the ganoine; g, ganoine; mt, microtubercules on the ganoine surface; p, punctuations on the ganoine cover (pores in cross section); ri, ridges in the ganoine cover." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/280089/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.280090>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. A, Scanning Electron Microscopic image of a fulcral scale of the caudal peduncle in cross-section. B – C, Light microscope photographs of trunk scales in cross-section. Abbreviations: de, dentine; g, ganoine; is, isopedine; od, odontodes; p, pores on the ganoine (punctuations of the surface); vc, vascular canal; zs, zone of superposition of the ganoine." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/280090/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

